# UX Rules

## Navigation

### Large / Complex Entities (nhiều field, có content, media)
- Use full page flow:
  List → Detail → Edit
- Do NOT use modal
- Example:
  - Article
  - Place
  - Job
  - Event

---

### Simple Entities (ít field, cấu hình đơn giản)
- Use modal for Create/Edit
- No need for detail page
- Example:
  - Category
  - Tag
  - Lookup data
  - Settings

---

## Decision Rule

Use modal IF:
- ≤ 5–6 fields
- No rich content (editor, upload…)
- No complex relationships

Use full page IF:
- Has content editor
- Has images/media
- Has SEO fields
- Has multiple sections

---

## Form UX

- Auto generate slug from title
- Validate inline
- Show errors clearly

---

## Feedback

- Show success toast after save
- Confirm before delete

---

## Remote / API calls (Razor Pages + ABP JS)

When the UI calls the backend (application service via client proxy, `abp.ajax`, uploads, etc.):

- Wrap the operation with **`abp.ui.setBusy`** on the relevant container (form, card, or `null` for whole page) and **`abp.ui.clearBusy`** when finished (use `.always` / `.finally` so busy clears on both success and failure).
- On **failure**, show **`abp.notify.error`** with the server message when available (e.g. `error.message` from ABP remote exception response); avoid silent failures.
- On **success**, use **`abp.notify.success`** when it helps the user (save, delete, upload).

Docs: [Notify](https://abp.io/docs/latest/framework/ui/mvc-razor-pages/javascript-api/notify), [Block / Busy](https://abp.io/docs/latest/framework/ui/mvc-razor-pages/javascript-api/block-busy).

---

## Empty State

- Show:
  "No data yet"
  + Create button



  ## UX Priority

- Always prefer usability over consistency
- Avoid forcing modal or page blindly
- Choose the simplest UI that fits the data complexity